How does education contribute to the success of societies according to the following C++ code?
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
  int education = 10; // hypothetical education level
  int success = 0; // hypothetical measure of societal success
  if (education > 8) {
    success += 5;
  }
  cout << "The societal success level is: " << success << endl;
  return 0;
} 
In the above code, we have a hypothetical measure of societal success and a hypothetical education level. If the education level is greater than 8 (out of 10), we add 5 to the success level. Based on this code, how does education contribute to the success of societies?
